commit.message:
Re-work markdown fenced codeblock lexing

This primarily makes lexing of nested fenced codeblocks work but also added support for tilde-delimited blocks and corrected the end offset for blocks.
Helpers to show start and end,  line and column, when checking lexed Regions
Remove redundant type union
Prepare for 6.0.3 release
Add fixes for Pytest 8.0.0
Add CI for pytest 7 and 8 separately
Prepare for 6.0.2 release
Add test for texting directive with multiple lines of trailing whitespace
Unused import
Drop usage of py.path.local
Prepare for 6.0.1 release
Fix lexing of ReST directives without whitespace between them
Prepare for 6.0.0 release
Official support for Python 3.12
Collapse LexedRegion into Region
Make Region.evaluator optional
Examples of how to add more functionality by subclassing
Abstract duplicated code into a LexerCollection class
ReST options don't require a value
Remove unneeded annotations
Fix parsing of MyST directive options with no leading whitespace
Fix parsing of Markdown fenced codeblocks at the end of documents with no training newline

MyST DirectiveLexer now extracts options

This includes yaml options.

Implement Markdown Parsers

This is a subset of the MyST parsers, targeting CommonMark and GFM

Abstract out a PythonDocTestOrCodeBlockParser

This is used in Markdown variants.
Fix name of unittest tests in myst functional example

Add py.typed package data

This tells type checkers that the type annotations should be read from the Python implementation of `sybil`.
See https://mypy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installed_packages.html#creating-pep-561-compatible-packages for an example description of adding `py.typed` to a project which uses `setuptools` and `setup.py`.

If you would really like CI to enforce this, look at using `pyright --verifytypes sybil`.

Ignore sybil.integration.pytest

This file is mainly pytest internals where unit tests catch things, not typing
Implicit return of None is fine
Disable unwanted union-attr warnings
